    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "That example is a very simplified version of my real use case. The real use case is that we do have a full react client side application we are migrating to nextjs, and we need SSR in most of the case (which are handled today by prerender.io)\nSo we have a lot of existing component which are totally autonomous, we can put them anywhere in the website, they currently embed their own InstantSearch, their own client, it could be any indices, with any configuration, even not the same api key (we use dynamic keys for logged users)\n\nI've juste migrated them using InstantSearchNext instead of InstantSearch and expected to keep the same usage.\n\nIf not supported, I think the documentation should said it somewhere, because it's a step back from the regular client side only InstantSearch which we do use currently.\n",
    "created_at": "2026-01-27T08:35:54Z",
